label: Maternal coping strategy index
definition: Coping strategy index assessed at baseline. Measures household food security. A higher value indicates higher insecurity

label: Unhidden self-control task time
definition: Time from when a treat was placed openly in front of the child to when they took it. Self-control was defined as a child who waited for 2 minutes.

label: A-not-B score
definition: To assess object permanence and working memory, the child watched as a treat was hidden under 1 of 2 bowls (A or B); after a brief delay, the child was asked to find the treat under one of the bowls, remembering where it was. The exercise was repeated 10 times, switching which bowl the treat was hidden under according to protocol for all 10 episodes to check that the child had no perseveration error. The score reflects the number of times they correctly identified where a treat was hidden out of 10 episodes.

label: Hidden self-control task time
definition: Time from when a treat was hidden in front of the child to when they took it. Self-control was defined as a child who waited for 2 minutes

label: Maternal decision making autonomy score
definition: Choice or control in decisions and access to resources that affect the mother herself or her children. Higher values indicate greater decision making. Questions were taken from the Zimbabwe Demographic and Health Survey 2015 and ask whether a mother can make a decision on her own to purchase 7 items of varying value. Assessed at baseline
